T1  - Constructive and Destructive Deviance tn Organizations
AU  - Warren, Danielle E.
Y1  - 2003/10/01
PY  - 2003
DA  - 2003/10/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/amr.2003.10899440
DO  - 10.5465/amr.2003.10899440
T2  - Academy of Management Review
JF  - Academy of Management Review
JO  - AMR
SP  - 622
EP  - 632
VL  - 28
IS  - 4
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - There are two streams of research on deviance in the management literature, one on its positive effects and one on its negative effects. Although the underlying behavior is the same?a departure from norms?these two research streams remain separate. Here I review the literature, develop an integrative typology of deviance, and call for further advancements with respect to identifying reference groups and establishing normative standards.
AB  - There are two streams of research on deviance in the management literature, one on its positive effects and one on its negative effects. Although the underlying behavior is the same?a departure from norms?these two research streams remain separate. Here I review the literature, develop an integrative typology of deviance, and call for further advancements with respect to identifying reference groups and establishing normative standards.
